SERVLET :- 

     A Servlet is a Java class that runs on a server and handles client requests (usually HTTP) to generate dynamic web content. 
     It acts as the middle layer between a client (browser) and a database or application logic.

     In simple words we can say that :-
             Think of a Servlet as Java powered waiter - in this the client places an order (requests)  ,  the waiter takes it to the kitchen(business logic)  ,  and bring backs the food (response) .
    